summary: 01/22/1993: A bomb blast in Hyderabad, Pakistan killed 22 people, injured 100, and caused substantial damage to the surrounding area. No group claimed the attack, but police suspected the Jeay Sindh group.
addnotes: Hyderabad is the second-largest city in Sindh Province and had been the center of political and ethnic violence for nearly a decade. The extremist group Jeay Sindh, which demands statehood for Sindh, had been blamed for much of the violence.
scite1: “Bomb blast kill 22, injure 100 in Pakistan,” Chicago Tribune, January 24, 1993.
scite2: “Two bomb blast kill 22, injure 100,” The Associated Press, January 23, 1993.
